==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purport
<hw>Pur"port</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>purport</ets>; <ets>pur</ets>, <ets>pour</ets>, for (L.
<ets>pro</ets>) + <ets>porter</ets> to bear, carry. See <er>Port</er>
demeanor.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Design or tendency; meaning; import;
tenor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whole scope and <qex>purport</qex> of that dialogue.
<qex>Norris</qex>.⟦br⟧
With a look so piteous in <qex>purport</qex>⟦br⟧
As if he had been loosed out of hell.</q> <rj><qau> Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disguise; covering.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For she her sex under that strange <qex>purport</qex>⟦br⟧
Did use to hide.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purport</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Purport
<hw>Pur"port</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Purported</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Purporting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>purporter</ets>,
<ets>pourporter</ets>. See <er>Purport</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To intend to show; to intend; to mean; to signify; to import; --
often with an object clause or infinitive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They in most grave and solemn wise unfolded⟦br⟧
Matter which little <qex>purported</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Rowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purportless</ent>⟦br⟧
